mad? OK. Just get dressed. I'm
sorry you're

24:43.048 --> 24:44.550 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
crying.

24:44.650 --> 24:48.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: I met with
Delaney Ruston
last week in Washington, D.C.

24:48.387 --> 24:52.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I wonder, what was that --
initially, what
made you want to do this film?

24:52.291 --> 24:56.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. DELANEY RUSTON: Well, I was
having a really
hard time as a mom with my two
kids. You know,

24:56.895 --> 25:01.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
my son wanted to play video
games a lot and
my daughter really wanted more
and more social

25:01.567 --> 25:04.603 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
media, and I felt completely out
of control.

25:04.703 --> 25:10.376 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, as a doctor, I was
thinking, what is
the impact of all this screen
time? I knew,

25:10.476 --> 25:15.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
