on a physiological level. It's
not just psychological.

26:29.555 --> 26:32.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: We exposed young mice to
switching sounds
and light.

26:33.091 --> 26:37.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In the film,
Ruston talks
with researchers who are
studying what multitasking,

26:37.329 --> 26:42.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
switching rapidly back and forth
between digital
devices, does to the brain
function of mice.

26:42.434 --> 26:46.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Afterwards, we looked at
the effect on
learning and found that the
ability of these

26:46.505 --> 26:52.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
young mice to learn new things
