learning offline, social
engagement, competency,

27:36.088 --> 27:37.856 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
talking to people face to face.

27:37.956 --> 27:42.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think, if we're giving
them a lot of
those situations, that even if
there's some

27:42.528 --> 27:49.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
concern about attention span and
possibly
some changes in the brain, I
think that humans

27:49.334 --> 27:54.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are resilient enough -- and
already we're
seeing that people are not, you
know, dropping

27:54.239 --> 27:58.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
